<br>
Now my favorite place to farm plat, is of course Rathe Mountains.  So I am enroute to RM. As I'm walking thru SK- WHO DO I RUN INTO?!?!  Yes, it was the winged horse!  No time to cast a pet, it needed to die now.  with 2 quick nukes, Quillmane was no more.<br>
<br>
As I aproach to loot, I prepared myself for disapointment.  I knew that Quillmane was a rare spawn, and its cloak even rarer. Well my fellow Magi, I was the luckiest Magician on Povar, to be the new owner of the Cloak!  <br>
<br>
So the next day, I go up on a Hate raid with a guild I am applying for.  Once we got settled in, I asked a ranger if he see's MagiTpasa up.  He bares the bad news, &quot;Sorry, No&quot;.  <br>
<br>
While cleared out Hate, I thought of the my luck in SK.  How Ironic.  After giving up all hope , and resorting to a plan of MQing, the winged horse just strolls right past me!  (For all wanting to know, I found him just east of paw)<br>
<br>
Anyway, 2 hours later, we are on the 2nd floor of Hate.  Only a few more mobs to pull before everything is cleared.  Then the puller shouts &quot;Magi T'Pasa is up! and holding the staff!&quot;  Before the pull even reached us, I had /tells of &quot;congrats&quot;.<br>
<br>
Later on that evening - I turned in all my peices.  And Povar now has another Epiced Mage.  <br>
<br>
The quest has taken me over a year to complete.  And is something every Magi should obtain.  It is true what they say, this pet is a MONSTER!<br>
<br>
I would like to thank:<br>
<br>
My good friend Dafier, for without him, my epic would never of happened.  <br>
<br>
To the Utopian guild, for having me up in Hate, they really are a great bunch of people.  <br>
<br>
To the Asatru guild.  <br>
<br>
And of course to that lil gnome wizard who took me up to PoA.<br>
<br>
Goodluck fellow Magi!<br>
<br>
Casima - 60 Magician (Povar)<br>
